Title: Restricted-Orientation Halfspaces  
Author: Eugene Fink Derick Wood 
Keyword: computational geometry, mathematical foundations, generalized convexity, restricted ori entations, three dimensions.  
Web: http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~eugene  http://www.cs.ust.hk/~dwood  
Address: Pittsburgh, PA 15213, USA  Hong Kong  
Affiliation: School of Computer Science Carnegie Mellon University  Department of Computer Science Hong Kong Univ. of Science and Technology Clear Water Bay, Kowloon,  
Abstract: Restricted-orientation convexity, also called O-convexity, is the study of geometric objects whose intersection with lines from some fixed set is empty or connected. We introduce restricted-orientation halfspaces, which are an O-convexity analog of halfspaces, explore their properties, and demonstrate their relationship to restricted-orientation convex sets. 
